  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together yogurt, lemon juice, garlic, cumin, coriander, red pepper flakes, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the beef strips to the bowl and mix well to coat with the yogurt sauce.",
    "Transfer the beef to a baking sheet lined with parchment paper and bake for 15 minutes or until cooked through.",
    "Meanwhile, crumble the feta cheese into a small bowl and microwave for 10-15 seconds or until slightly melted.",
    "To assemble the bowls, place a portion of the cooked beef onto a plate or bowl, followed by a dollop of the yogurt sauce, and top with crumbled feta cheese, chopped parsley, cucumber, and tomato.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy!"
